Spring + JPA + hibernate.
JPA - Jakarata Persistance API - interfaces
hibernate - this will have iplementation classes.

@Entity - This class level annotation. 
This tells JPA that this class is blueprint od DB table

@Table - This allows to specifiy database table name. If class Name and DB table name are different then 
use @Table to map table to class.

@Id - This field level annotation. 
Give this annotation to primary key column

@GeneratedValue - This field level annotation. 
If you dont want to manually assign a value to colum every time to save object. this annoatation will automatically generates id value.

@Column
It matches field name to DB column name. 
@Repostory
  This marks a class as DAO(Data access Object), this class will have operations to insert, update, delete, retrieve data. 
@Trasaction.
   DB operation should be all or nothing.


